===Etymology 1===
{{L.}} '''[[moneta|monēta]]''', "place for making coins", from the temple of Juno Moneta (named for '''[[Moneta|Monēta]]''', mother of the Muses), where coins were made.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A building or institution where money (originally, only [[coin]]s) is produced under government licence.
# {{context|informal}} A large amount of money.
#: ''That house is worth a mint''
#: ''It must have cost a mint to produce!''

